<item>
            <title>[LOG4J2-1262] Log4jServletContextListener unnecessary exception</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LOG4J2-1262</link>
                <project id="12310790" key="LOG4J2">Log4j 2</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;tt&gt;Log4jServletContextListener.contextDestroyed&lt;/tt&gt; throws an &lt;tt&gt;IllegalStateException&lt;/tt&gt; if contextInitialized was never called. In certain rare situations where a server startup fails due to previous errors this Exception is unnecessary.&lt;br/&gt;
So I suggest to now throw an Exception and instead log it as a warning and end the method gracefully.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
